[
  {
    "id" : "9fd2b334-e348-4921-9421-4344e669862f",
    "prId" : 13326,
    "prUrl" : "https://github.com/conda-forge/staged-recipes/pull/13326#pullrequestreview-539550539",
    "prSource" : "GitHub",
    "comments" : [
      {
        "id" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "parentId" : null,
        "authorId" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "body" : "Any reason not to add `noarch:python` here?",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-25T21:54:32Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "f8538e83-121e-4df8-af20-4bbe110d4eb5",
        "parentId" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "authorId" : "ed19f9c6-167e-4152-ac15-977146dc2a70",
        "body" : "I think `grayskull` left out the `noarch:python` because benedict's `setup.py` defines a pinned version for `ftfy` on python 2.7.\r\n\r\nI've fixed the `ftfy` entries in requirements/run, and my understanding is that we don't want `noarch:python` here.\r\n\r\nOne thing I wasn't sure of is whether or not `skip: true  # [py<27]` is actually needed?",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-26T04:57:16Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed19f9c6-167e-4152-ac15-977146dc2a70",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "63c2b95a-9ae2-4fae-b214-0a0ce45d7859",
        "parentId" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "authorId" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "body" : "No, as is this recipe can't be noarch python. However, by default conda-forge is not building Python 2.7 packages--do you have need for the Python 2.7 support?",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-26T05:46:38Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "4a99c784-9c10-4370-b019-f3bc4842625f",
        "parentId" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "authorId" : "ed19f9c6-167e-4152-ac15-977146dc2a70",
        "body" : "Not particularly, `noarch: python` and `python >=3.4` would work fine for us if that is preferred at this point.",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-26T05:50:01Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed19f9c6-167e-4152-ac15-977146dc2a70",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "f39d5e02-51b1-48f6-b5f1-ae5e0a25002d",
        "parentId" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "authorId" : "ed19f9c6-167e-4152-ac15-977146dc2a70",
        "body" : "(or whatever the default min python3 version is for conda-forge now)",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-26T05:50:38Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "ed19f9c6-167e-4152-ac15-977146dc2a70",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "bf11ea26-ca5f-4bf0-9b64-2f0b80316f10",
        "parentId" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "authorId" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "body" : "The big thing is that with noarch, only one package needs to be built. Without it, you need a package for every supported combination of architecture and Python version including PyPy (currently over a dozen). ",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-26T21:10:06Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "4430bd38-09a2-441e-a206-ffb81802f1c1",
        "parentId" : "cdda9598-7abd-42ba-bc6c-8105bbedbc9d",
        "authorId" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "body" : "So yes, if you could make it noarch and `python >=3.4` (or whatever works for you--we're only building new packages for >=3.6, but it doesn't matter much for noarch so long as the code runs) that would be greatly preferable.",
        "createdAt" : "2020-11-26T21:12:10Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2020-11-27T00:23:09Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "f2a8b72f-e001-4606-a1c7-b774f81c945f",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      }
    ],
    "commit" : "c2c61aa0083e3696dae6b3732aa41f2c1ce0b071",
    "line" : 14,
    "diffHunk" : "@@ -1,1 +12,16 @@\nbuild:\n  number: 0\n  noarch: python\n  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv"
  },
